\par Claus:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f40\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid5510798\charrsid5510798 None at all. And, in fact, it was totally negative from that point of view. Sorry, you\rquote re going to be very bored, but that
\rquote s not my problem! My father was a banker, and he was rather keen that I should become a banker, and when we came to England, and when I\rquote d been t
o school here, and when I finished school, it was a question of what to do, and my father had some business connections and he thought the nearest I could get to banking the better, and he knew somebody in Sainsbury\rquote 
s, and he knew somebody in Lyons, so I had interviews with Lyons, with one of the Salmon family. We were now in war, and he immediately said, \'93Look, you\rquote re still German, can\rquote t take you into our Company\'94 \endash  that\rquote 
s a brief summary of that. I then had an interview with the Sainsbury family my father knew, and the same answer \endash  \'93You\rquote re still German\'94
. I was, strictly speaking, stateless, but from their point of view I was German. And the only thing he said was, \'93You have a very nice voice, nice accent, and so maybe in due course we\rquote ll take you, and we 
would start you off in Victoria Street, Sainsbury\'94 \endash  because they need people with nice voices and so on. What my father really had in mind, he said I would end up as Head of the Savoy or something like that \endash  a hotel, I\rquote 
d always liked hotels, and he thought I would be good. That\rquote s commercial, which is what he wanted for me - and it also has music in the foyer - perfect! But it didn\rquote t come off. So for lack of something else to do, he said \endash 
 those were the days when fathers decided really, you know \endash  \'93Why don\rquote t you go to LSE and study commerce? At least then you\rquote ll be ready in due course\'94
. And so I enrolled at LSE, 1940 was the year, to do commerce, a B.Com. And why statistics? Well, the reason for that was, before I could go to LSE I was interned. I won\rquote t go on any of the sidelines unless you ask me. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 
\ltrch\fcs0 \b\f40\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid5510798\charrsid5510798 
