t remember enough about it. In terms of publications as a statistician, obviously what I\rquote m most proud of is my book on survey methods, which later on became - I got one of my colleagues to 
do the third edition. But that was published in 1957, and I was quite a young academic, and forgive me for saying it straight, but it remains a standard book on survey methods now in 2012! I get royalties all the time, it\rquote s unbelievable! }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f40\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid5510798\charrsid5510798 
