\par Claus:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f40\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid5510798\charrsid5510798 Well, I don\rquote 
t think so, because I was quite close to the Gallup Poll people, a guy called Henry Durant, who ran it, and with Ruth Glass \endash  the wife of David Glass, the demographer. I can\rquote 
t now remember whether I did any surveys, it would have had to have been in the fifties - I was involved in doing surveys with the Gallup group, but I don\rquote t remember whether any of them were sort of my own, so to speak. 
What did we decide about transport? Jennifer [Wingate]: I want to ask something. I\rquote d like to know how you go about discovering the potential in a society. It\rquote s so abstract. It\rquote 
s almost like tapping or putting a value on the streams and the mountains, which is something that we don\rquote t - can you ask Claus that? I\rquote d just love to know! }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\b\f40\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid5510798\charrsid5510798 
